<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Administration - xarBB</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <img src="modules/adminpanels/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
			<xar:mlstring>xarbb provides basic forum functions provided mainly from Xaraya utility modules.  The forum itself is very light weight, but designed to handle large volume postings.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>
			From the menu, you have three choices.  "Modify Configuration", "Add Forums", and "View Forums". 
			</xar:mlstring>
			<ul>
				<li><xar:mlstring>Modify Configuration -- Allows you to set certain configuration routines for forums.</xar:mlstring></li>
				<li><xar:mlstring>View Forums -- Allows you to view the forums that you have configured on your system.</xar:mlstring></li>
				<li><xar:mlstring>Add Forums -- Allows you to add new forums to your system.</xar:mlstring></li>
			</ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>There are no included blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>There are no included hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
